<br>
Which basically seemed to be most people's problem with the spell.  Everytime someone pulled out a parse of a charmed pet doing 400-1000dps, it was a pet that was hasted everytime.  Hasted pets were also what helped Enchanters to duo bosses.  Faster damage allowed you to get a mob down before charm's duration would fade.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> They did NOTHING to really change Enchanters solo ability, so they didn't nerf this ability with chanters at all.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So unless it makes it impossible for Enchanters to be able to solo, it's not a nerf?  You don't think making it so charm will be resisted a ton more often (and I know how much more since my mezzes have the same resist adj as the charm on Test) or having charm fade more often isn't a nerf?<br>
<br>
I honestly don't understand why so many people have such a huge problem with Enchanters soloing.  It's not a new ability we were given with PoP.  I soloed in the original game and Kunark and Velious and Luclin.  <br>
<br>
I suppose all the exaggerations of Enchanters getting 2-3 AAs an hour would upset some people, but being an Enchanter that solos in the Planes, I honestly don't think these claims are true.  None of the other Enchanters that solo that I know have even come close to getting an AA this fast.  If it is true, it probably has to be under perfect, unique circumstances and with a hasted pet.  Honestly, I'd say unless you've sat and watched an Enchanter solo and AA firsthand, you've probably been fed a lot of exaggerations (by other classes <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Enchanters) on stuff.  Just to give you an example, I had a Wizard in HoH tell me he gets almost a full AA per quad, which I know isn't true since I know how much exp each mob gives solo.<br>
<br>
Regardless though, I see Wizards and Druids quadding in PoP.  I've seen Mages, Rangers, Bards, Necromancers, Shadow Knights, Beastlords, and Shamans all soloing in PoP.  Why shouldn't Enchanters be allowed to solo too? <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The original reason that Necros were such great soloers was primarily because they were such crappy additions to groups. Their entire spell line was self-serving and thus, they were rewarded with great soloing power.<br>
<br>
Nowadays, this relationship no longer seems true, where is it possible for one class to be nearly essential for groups but can also be the best soloers at will.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Necromancers were also given a lot of new spells that made them more desirable in groups (group lich taps.  Clerics, another good group class, were given a lot of useful tools to help them solo.  I think instead of trying to get a class nerfed because they are good in groups and can solo, you should perhaps focus on trying to get Sony to balance out your abilities to solo and benefits in groups.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
<br>
I'd have to say though that I think a lot of people are reading too much into things.  Lucy <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>only</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> shows <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>spell changes</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  You have no clue if things were retooled to fix issues people had.  For all you know boss mobs in BoT now summon 4 giants to help them everytime you engage.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>EDIT:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> All you can see is the spell side of things.  When mobs in AC were made immune to stun so that people could no longer AE them, there was no indication of that on Lucy's.<br>
<br>
IMO there were a lot of areas where the problem was less to do with Charm and more to do with the encounter.  Fpr example, you shouldn't be able to zone in and out a few times to kill a mob b/c it regens extremely slowly. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
